I am pleased to report that key leaders in the House & Senate understand the need to prevent PR from falling off the Obamacare MedicaidCliff
The first bill that I sponsored, H.R. 259, would translate into law the Task Force’s most significant recommendation.
I am working on the legislation with the Members of the House and the Senate who served on the Task Force.
Since the first day after I was sworn in as a Member of Congress, I have introduced bills to implement those recommendations.
No other Resident Commissioner had a bipartisan congressional report on the island like I have.
I am committed to pursuing the report’s recommendations.
Evidently, this is the consequence and price to pay for Puerto Rico not being a State, and it is a steep price indeed.
It also concluded that PR entities fare very poorly when applying for Fed competitive programs relative to entities in other US jurisdiction
The resulting report identified no less than 40 formula-based Federal programs where PR is treated differently .
TaskForce worked across party lines to come up w/ policy recommendations that could be implemented by the Fed gov to help PR economy grow
